tinued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":6,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":15,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":50,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705190,"age":81,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705191,"age":106,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":119,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When William Tokett was born in 1209, in Cumberland, England, his father, Roger Tokett, was 50 and his mother, Mrs. Roger Tokett, was 46. He married Mrs. Tokett about 1228, in Carlisle, Cumberland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1209–":"1209–Surnud","1186–1212":"1186–1212","1209–Male":"1209–Surnud","1211–Female":"1211–Surnud","1235–Female":"1235–Surnud","1160–1186":"1160–1186","1164–Female":"1164–Surnud","1164":"1164","1186":"1186","1160":"1160","Abt 1228":"umbes 1228","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","ABT 1185":"umbes 1185","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1211":"1211","1209":"1209","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Carlisle, Cumberland, England":"Carlisle, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"1209–":"1209–Kuollut","1186–1212":"1186–1212","1209–Male":"1209–Kuollut","1211–Female":"1211–Kuollut","1235–Female":"1235–Kuollut","1160–1186":"1160–1186","1164–Female":"1164–Kuollut","1164":"1164","1186":"1186","1160":"1160","Abt 1228":"noin 1228","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","ABT 1185":"noin 1185","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1212","1211":"1211","1209":"1209","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Carlisle, Cumberland, England":"Carlisle, Cumberland, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fr":{"1209–":"1209–Décédé","1186–1212":"1186–1212","1209–Male":"1209–Décédé","1211–Female":"1211–Décédée","1235–Female":"1235–Décédée","1160–1186":"1160–1186","1164–Female":"1164–Décédée","1164":"1164","1186":"1186","1160":"1160","Abt 1228":"environ 1228","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","ABT 1185":"environ 1185","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1212":"1